  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Niger Initial Malian Refugee Influx Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a response to the Malian refugee influx into Niger. Due to the conflict in Mali, there has been an increase in refugees leaving to Niger. Not all the refugees have been registered by UNHCR and some are lacking support. We will be looking at providing food relief as well as hygiene and cholera prevention kits to households.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We will be focusing on improving the living conditions of 55 households of Malian refugees. The distribution will include food supplies for two months with two distributions a month apart as well as a one-time distribution of a hygiene kit. The hygiene kits will include soaps, aquatabs, and mosquito nets to help prevent the spread of cholera. We will also be running several sessions on hygiene and cholera prevention.</narrative>
  </description>
